msgid ""
"<p>This panel shows data for instances running Splunk Enterprise "
"6.4+.</p><p><b>Service Time: </b>The time for the device to execute the "
"requests.</p><p><b>Wait Time: </b>I/O queue + execution time for requests"
" to complete. This reflects the end-to-end time spent on the "
"requests.</p><p><b>Storage I/O Saturation: </b>Percentage of time the CPU"
" was servicing requests. Disk saturation occurs when this value is close "
"to 100%. </p><p><b>Storage I/O Saturation (NFS): </b>Percentage of time "
"network resources were used to serve requests. Only applies to NFS disks."
" </p><p><a href=\"/help?location=learnmore.dmc.ru_machine.iostats\" "
"target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a> about the source of this data. </p>"
